Updated review: 7/28/20 Oh how we missed this place. It's been a couple of months since my family was here dining at the back of the restaurant pre-covid.  So we're thrilled to see it open when we drove by last week and chose to dine alfresco as it has a couple of bar tables and benches at the front of the restaurant. We appreciate this family owned pizza restaurant and we've always enjoyed their delicious pizzas. Our favorites are the thin and juicy Fresh mozzarella drizzled with homemade pesto sauce pizza and their Grandma's pizza. Please continue to support them if you're in the area. I know you'll not regret it.  Older review: 11/19 A wonderful place to support kind of a mom & pop/family with a mutiple generations  serving at the pizza store. South Slopers you're so lucky to have this cute eatery in your neighborhood and the best is, it is serving SUPER delicious pizzas at a price that won't burn your wallet.
